    when Captain Emil Richards, a naval officer turned merchant, established one of the first copper export routes in the region.

    Through the 18th and 19th centuries, the Richards name became synonymous with industry, progress, and philanthropy. Their estate on
    Slitøya Island—originally a simple coastal manor—grew into a sprawling property complete with private docks, greenhouses, and even
